    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1889-03-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1889-03-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="157"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d157">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Blaine</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1889-03-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 23, 1889</date>. (Received April
                        2.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 966.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to Mr. Bayard’s instruction No. 1089,
                    of the 1st instant, respecting the shipment of seamen on American vessels in
                    Canadian ports, I have the honor to acquaint you that I lost no time in
                    communicating a copy of the same to Her Majesty’s Government.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry White</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
